{{Other places3|Pembroke Street (disambiguation)}}

[[File:ModernArtOxford.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Modern Art Oxford]] on Pembroke Street.]]

'''Pembroke Street''' is in central [[Oxford]], [[England]]. [[St Ebbes Street]] is to the west and major thoroughfare of [[St Aldate's, Oxford|St Aldate's]] is to the east.

[[Modern Art Oxford]] (formerly the Museum of Modern Art) is located on the north side of the street (No 30).<ref>[http://www.modernartoxford.org.uk/ Modern Art Oxford, 30 Pembroke Street], including [http://www.modernartoxford.org.uk/Find/ How to Find Us].</ref> [[Greene's Tutorial College]] is at 45 Pembroke Street<ref>[http://www.greenes.org.uk/ Greene's Tutorial College], 45 Pembroke Street.</ref> and All Nations Language School is at No 40.<ref>[http://www.language-course-directory.com/language-schools/oxford.html All Nations Language School], 40 Pembroke Street.</ref>

[[Pembroke Square, Oxford|Pembroke Square]] and [[Pembroke College, Oxford|Pembroke College]] are close by to the south.

In November 2009, it was announced that the planned [[Story Museum]] would move to premises at Rochester House in Pembroke Street, using a gift of £2.5m from a private donor.<ref>[http://www.oxfordinspires.org/EE/index.php/site/news-item/story_museum_gets_anonymous_gift_to_buy_permanant_home/ News: Story Museum gets anonymous gift to buy permanent home in Oxford] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727160853/http://www.oxfordinspires.org/EE/index.php/site/news-item/story_museum_gets_anonymous_gift_to_buy_permanant_home/ |date=27 July 2011 }}, ''[http://www.oxfordinspires.org/ Oxford Inspires] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100323130925/http://www.oxfordinspires.org/ |date=23 March 2010 }}'', 19 November 2009.</ref>

